race.comment: HOLY HELL (8) is another decent winning chance for the in-form Seib stable. She's raced well in town and placed heavily bet at Wagga before the spell. Resumed with a nose defeat at Moruya as a short-priced favourite and with the extra fitness will take plenty of beating.  LYSANDER (11) led beaten a half length at Canberra in a 55 making good improvement. He won't have to find too much more to be in the finish at a decent p[price. EAST HARLEM (9) spiked his numbers just missing at Cootamundra and that reads well enough. Has a handy gate and always puts in. SCOPICS (2) is going okay and has been tried twice in town recently. Has the first-time blinkers applied today and they may spark the improvement required.
